main event: An object resembling a missile nose cone was tracked on radar and observed visually in Tulsa, Oklahoma on 17-18 January 1958.
interesting points: The object was tracked on radar as a missile nose cone when it was forwarded for analysis., Physical analysis confirmed that the object was actually a pipe or plumbing conduit., A handwritten letter reported the object was believed to be the size of a 'Jupiter C' missile and hovered silently., The investigation revealed that the object was most likely a natural phenomenon rather than man-made., There were no visible markings on the object that would identify it as a manufactured item.
sighted object: an object resembling a missile nose cone
witness description: Mr. Teeple, who observed an object he described as a rock approximately 6 inches in diameter.
